  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bic Banco H&amp;E</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BicBanco is a leading Brazilian mid-sized bank, which has operated predominantly in the middle market niche since 1938.  It is publicly traded at BM&amp;FBovespa, and has a nation-wide presence with 39 branches in all regions of Brazil. The project entails a corporate loan for which use of proceeds will be on-lending to health and education small and medium enterprises.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is expected to: expand access to credit to health and education SMEs through a wholesaling approach; enhance BicBancos service capacity by providing IFC industry expertise (best practices) and contacts; support the developing access by the population to health &amp; education services; lend credibility to the market by reaching smaller institutions with competitive products; and help strengthen the competitiveness of H&amp;E mid-sized companies.</narrative>
  </description>
